cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SE 

This paper is about a neural encoder-decoder model with reinforcement learning for grammatical error correction, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The use of reinforcement learning also suggests that the paper may belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, since the paper proposes a new model for a specific task, it may also be relevant to cs.SE (Software Engineering).
